1. What is Nested Class?

A nested class is a class declared inside another class.

Example:

class Outer {

    class Inner {

    }

}

Here:

Outer = outer class
Inner = nested class

Why use it?

Logical grouping
Better encapsulation
Inner class can access outer class members
Helps hide implementation details
2. Types of Nested Classes

Java has 4 types:

Nested Class
|
|---- 1. Static Nested Class
|
|---- 2. Non-static Inner Class
|
|---- 3. Local Inner Class
|
|---- 4. Anonymous Inner Class
3. Static Nested Class

A nested class with static keyword.

Example:

class Outer {


    static class Inner {

        void show(){
            System.out.println("Hello");
        }

    }

}
How to create object?

Important point:

Static nested class does NOT need outer object.

Create:

Outer.Inner obj = new Outer.Inner();

obj.show();

Why?

Because static belongs to class.

Same as:

Math.sqrt()

You don't create Math object.

