4. Static Nested Class Access Rules

Example:

class Outer {

static int x=100;

int y=200;


static class Inner {


void display(){

System.out.println(x);

}

}

}

Output:

100

Static inner class can access:

✅ static members directly

But:

System.out.println(y);

Error.

Why?

Because y belongs to object.

No Outer object exists.

To access non-static:

class Outer {


int y=200;


static class Inner {


void display(){

Outer obj=new Outer();

System.out.println(obj.y);

}


}


}
5. Access Modifiers in Static Nested Class

Allowed:

public static class Inner

protected static class Inner

private static class Inner

static class Inner

All allowed.

Because nested class is a member of outer class.

Example:

class Outer {


private static class Inner {


}


}

Can outside access?

No:

Outer.Inner obj;

Error.

Because private.

6. Non-static Inner Class

Normal class inside class.

Example:

class Outer {


class Inner {


void show(){

System.out.println("Inner");

}


}


}
Object Creation

First outer object required.

Wrong:

Outer.Inner obj = new Outer.Inner();

Error.

Correct:

Outer outer = new Outer();

Outer.Inner inner = outer.new Inner();

inner.show();

Syntax is important:

outerObject.new Inner()
7. Why Outer Object Required?

Because inner class automatically keeps reference of outer object.

Internally:

class Outer$Inner {

    Outer this$0;

}

It knows:

"which Outer object created me"

Example:

class Outer {


int value=50;


class Inner {


void show(){

System.out.println(value);

}


}


}

Works.

Because inner class has outer reference.

8. Access Rules of Inner Class

Inner class can access everything:

class Outer {


private int a=10;

protected int b=20;

public int c=30;


class Inner{


void test(){

System.out.println(a);
System.out.println(b);
System.out.println(c);

}


}


}

All works.

Because inner class is part of outer class.

9. Can Inner Class have static members?

Before Java 16:

Only static final constants allowed.

Example:

class Outer {


class Inner {


static final int x=10;


}


}

Allowed.

Modern Java (Java 16+):

Static members allowed.

class Outer {


class Inner {


static int x=10;


}


}

Allowed.

10. Static Method inside Nested Class

Example:

class Outer {


static class Inner{


static void display(){

System.out.println("Hello");

}


}


}

Call:

Outer.Inner.display();

No object.

Because:

static → class level.

11. Non-static Method inside Nested Class

Example:

class Outer {


static class Inner{


void display(){

}


}


}

Call:

Outer.Inner obj = new Outer.Inner();

obj.display();

Because method is object level.

12. Final Nested Class

Example:

class Outer {


final class Inner {


}


}

Meaning:

Nobody can extend Inner.

Example:

class Child extends Outer.Inner
{

}

Not allowed.

13. Can Nested Class be Abstract?

Yes.

Example:

class Outer {


abstract class Inner {


abstract void show();


}


}

Child must implement.

14. Can Nested Class be Interface?

Yes.

Example:

class Outer {


interface Inner {


void show();


}


}
15. Local Inner Class

Class inside method.

Example:

class Outer {


void display(){


class Inner{


void show(){

System.out.println("Hi");

}


}


Inner obj=new Inner();

obj.show();


}


}

Scope only inside method.

Cannot access outside.

16. Local Inner Class Access

Can access:

Local variables only if final/effectively final.

Example:

void test(){

int x=10;


class Inner{

void show(){

System.out.println(x);

}

}


}

Works.

But:

x=20;

then error.

17. Anonymous Inner Class

No class name.

Example:

abstract class Animal {

abstract void sound();

}


class Test {


public static void main(String args[]){


Animal a=new Animal(){


void sound(){

System.out.println("Dog");

}


};


a.sound();


}


}

Output:

Dog
18. Nested Class + Inheritance

Example:

class Outer {


class Inner {


}


}


class Child extends Outer.Inner
{


}

Not directly possible.

Need Outer object:

Child(Outer o)
{
    o.super();
}

Advanced topic.

19. Static vs Non-static Inner Difference
Feature	Static Nested	Inner
static keyword	yes	no
Outer object required	no	yes
Access outer instance variable	no direct	yes
Memory reference	no	yes
Creation	Outer.Inner	outer.new Inner
